## Development

This project uses modern Python tooling:

- **[uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/)** for fast dependency management and virtual environments
- **[ruff](https://docs.astral.sh/ruff/)** for linting and code formatting
- **[pyright](https://github.com/microsoft/pyright)** for type checking
- **[pytest](https://docs.pytest.org/)** for testing
- **[prek](https://github.com/j178/prek)** for git hooks (drop-in `pre-commit` replacement)

### Setup

1. Install [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) and [prek](https://github.com/j178/prek) globally
2. Clone this repository
3. Run `uv sync --dev` to install dependencies
4. Run `prek install --install-hooks` to set up both pre-commit and pre-push hooks

### Commands

- `uv run pytest` - Run tests
- `uv run ruff check .` - Run linting
- `uv run ruff format .` - Format code
- `pyright` - Run type checking
- `prek run --all-files` - Run all hooks
{% if dependency_updates == "renovate" %}
### Dependency updates

This project uses [Renovate](https://docs.renovatebot.com/) to keep dependencies and pinned tool versions current. It reads `renovate.json`.
{% if ci_provider == "github" %}
Activate it with **one** of these (using both causes duplicate PRs):

- **Hosted app (recommended):** install the [Renovate GitHub App](https://github.com/apps/renovate) — free for public and private repos — then delete `.github/workflows/renovate.yml`.
- **Self-hosted:** keep the bundled `.github/workflows/renovate.yml` and add a `RENOVATE_TOKEN` repository secret (a PAT with `repo` + `workflow` scopes, or a GitHub App token).
{% elif ci_provider == "gitlab" %}
To activate it:

1. Add a masked `RENOVATE_TOKEN` CI/CD variable — a Project or Group Access Token with the `api` scope and Maintainer role.
2. Create a **pipeline schedule** (e.g. weekly) on your default branch. The `renovate` job runs only on scheduled pipelines.
{% else %}
Point a Renovate runner — the [hosted app](https://github.com/apps/renovate) or a scheduled CI job — at this repo and it will pick up `renovate.json`.
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

